                    <p class="mb-2 font-medium">"Social Network Material" (or "SNC") refers to the user-generated content you agree to publish via a Social Network, which may include, but is not limited to, Personal Information, such as digital sounds and photos you post to a Social Network. It also includes Personal Information that may be published on the pages of other users on Social Networks.</p>
                    <p class="mb-2 font-medium">"Organization", "we", "us", and "our" refer to the Book Author World.</p>
                    <p class="mb-2 font-medium">Third parties that are not Educational Partners and do not provide services to Book Author World are referred to as "Unrelated Entities."</p>
                    <p class="mb-2 font-medium">When you visit our Sites, we gather "web analytical information," which is information created by the internet. This data may be connected to marketing data and personal data. When connected to additional information that may be used to identify you personally, whether alone or in conjunction with other information, it is deemed Personal Information.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-[#a51f24] lg:text-[28px] md:text-[20px] text-[14px] font-[500] sitka mb-2 relative before:content-[''] before:w-20 before:h-[4px] before:bg-[#000000] before:absolute before:bottom-0">We Gather Information</h3>
                    <p class="mb-2 font-medium">When we chat to you on the phone, we gather different sorts of information from you via our Sites. Some of this data is acquired automatically through the Organization's usage of different online and internet technologies, including Social Networking applications.</p>
                    <p class="mb-2 font-medium">Other Information is collected when you respond to an advertisement or a request for information; when you register or order educational or other products and services, create a Social Network or other Site profile, or use one of our learning assessments or other interactive tools; or when you use one of our learning assessments or other interactive tools. Our Web Analytical Information allows us to observe how users locate and navigate our Sites, as well as their preferences for Site or Social Networking Content. It also shows us which pages users visit most frequently, allowing us to make our Sites more helpful and relevant. To achieve the goals, this information may be connected to personal information.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-[#a51f24] lg:text-[28px] md:text-[20px] text-[14px] font-[500] sitka mb-2 relative before:content-[''] before:w-20 before:h-[4px] before:bg-[#000000] before:absolute before:bottom-0">Automatically Gathered Information</h3>
                    <p class="mb-2 font-medium">Web Analytical Information is collected automatically each time you visit one of our Sites. This information does not, in general, identify you personally. Web analytical information includes, but is not limited to, the following:</p>
